"children":[
"Nonulcer Dyspepsia"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s7_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"44e253",
"children":[
"Nonulcer dyspepsia is defined as nonspecific upper abdominal discomfort or nausea not attributable to ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"peptic ulcer disease",
"children":[
"PUD"
]
},
" or ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastroesophageal reflux disease",
"children":[
"GERD"
]
},
"."
]
},
" Diagnosis is based on the presence of one or more of the following symptoms:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"723207",
"children":[
"bothersome postprandial fullness"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5d871e",
"children":[
"early satiety"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"504d17",
"children":[
"epigastric burning"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"279ab5",
"children":[
"Various drugs may cause dyspepsia, including ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
","
]
},
" antibiotics, bisphosphonates, and potassium supplements."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s7_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"dfcbb0",
"children":[
"Endoscopy is indicated only for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"cf2741",
"children":[
"patients aged ≥60 years"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8c3ac7",
"children":[
"younger patients at high risk for malignancy (multiple and severe alarm features or emigration from Asia, Russia, or South America)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s7_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e2b123",
"children":[
"If possible, discontinue all medications that cause dyspepsia."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"523735",
"children":[
"For patients aged ≤60 years without alarm features, implement a test-and-treat approach for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"08ab1b",
"children":[
"For those who test negative for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
", implement an empiric trial with a ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
" for 4 to 6 weeks."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5afb99",
"children":[
"Patients with refractory symptoms despite empiric therapy should undergo upper endoscopy."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
